{TEXT -1 56 "5.  Solving Systems of Equations in Several Variables.  \+
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 49 "When \+
we have an equation in two variables, e.g.  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x -2*y
 = 5" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"&" }{TEXT 
-1 147 "  we often associate with it a graph, the set of points (x,y) \+
in the two-dimensional plane which satisfy the equation.  For a linear
 equation like " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x-2*y = 5" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xG
F'F'*&\"\"#F'%\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"&" }{TEXT -1 89 " the graph is a straight
 line.  For more a complicated equation in two variables, e.g.,  " }
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "2*x^3 -3*x + y^2 = x*y" "6#/,(*&\"\"#\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"$
F'F'*&F*F'F)F'!\"\"*$%\"yGF&F'*&F)F'F.F'" }{TEXT -1 45 "  the graph be
comes a more complicated curve." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 282 "When we have two equations in two variab
les, we think of the solution set of this system of equations as being
 the set of points (x,y) which satisfy both equations simultaneously. \+
 In terms of their graphs, the solution set is the set of points where
 the graphs intersect (cross).  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 622 "When we have two linear equations in two
 variables, since their graphs are straight lines, then two straight l
ines, if they cross, will cross in exactly one place.  Hence, the solu
tion set of the system of equations will be exactly one point (x,y).  \+
If we have two equations which are more complicated, then the number o
f intersection points (crossing points) of their graphs can vary.  For
 example, if the graph of one equation is a circle and the graph of th
e other equation is a straight line, then, if their graphs cross, then
 number of solutions (intersection points) of the system of equations \+
could be 1 or 2.  Etc." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 128 "We can instruct Maple to find solutions of systems \+
of equations using the solve or fsolve commands.  The syntax for doing
 so is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
30 "     solve( \{eq1,eq2\}, \{x,y\});" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 "
 " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 85 "where eq1 and eq2 are equations in t
he variables x and y.  This is illustrated below." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 42 "solve(\{ x +
 2*y = 5, 2*x-3*y = -1\},\{x,y\});" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#
<$/%\"yG#\"#6\"\"(/%\"xG#\"#8F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "We could have defined " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 40 "eq1 := x + 2*y = 5;\neq2 := 2*x-3*y = -1;" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq1G/,&%\"xG\"\"\"*&\"\"#F(%\"yGF(F
(\"\"&" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$eq2G/,&*&\"\"#\"\"\"%\"xG
F)F)*&\"\"$F)%\"yGF)!\"\"F." }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 26 "and then given the command" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 
"" {MPLTEXT 1 0 25 "solve( \{eq1,eq2\}, \{x,y\});" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#<$/%\"yG#\"#6\"\"(/%\"xG#\"#8F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 55 "and achieved the same res
ult.  Remember the solution  (" }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "13/7" "6#*&\"#8\"\"\"
\"\"(!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "11/7" "6#*&\"#6\"\"\"\"\"
(!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 127 ") represents a point in the two-dimensional pla
ne (why two-dimensional?) where the graphs of the equations intersect \+
(cross).  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 63 "Find the solutions, if they exist, for the following equations \+
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "a.  " 
}{XPPEDIT 19 1 "3*x - 2*y = 6" "6#/,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'*&\"\"#F'%
\"yGF'!\"\"\"\"'" }{TEXT -1 3 ",  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "4*x + y = -2" "6#/
,&*&\"\"%\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'%\"yGF',$\"\"#!\"\"" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 4 "b.  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "6*x -9*y = 12" "6#/,&*&\"\"'\"\"\"%\"xGF'F
